</span></h1><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/What_are_the_five_key_questions_asked_by_the_CQC_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.jpg?v=1688138732" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/What_are_the_five_key_questions_asked_by_the_CQC_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.jpg?v=1688138732 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/What_are_the_five_key_questions_asked_by_the_CQC_-_Dr_Richard_Dune_500x.jpg?v=1688138732 320w" width="2000" height="1500" alt="What are the five key questions asked by the CQC - Dr Richard Dune -" title="What are the five key questions asked by the CQC - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-2920_"/></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-98da" data-category="Generic Content" data-name="Matcha" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-hAcGzb jHOovW pf-2921_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-eGPXGI cIlovf"><div class="sc-iCfMLu eehqFj pf-2922_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px;--s-sm:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-XxNYO eWQzGj pf-2923_"><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-2924_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-2926_">Every year, thousands of health and social care providers in England undergo inspections from the <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/blogs/dr-richard-dune/what-is-the-role-of-the-care-quality-commission" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);">Care Quality Commission (CQC)</span></i></a>, the independent regulator for these services. But what does the CQC look for? The answer is surprisingly simple: it all boils down to five key questions.<br>
<br>In this article, <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/dr-richard-dune-blog" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);">Dr Richard Dune</span></i></a> takes a deeper dive into these criteria and explains how they form the backbone of the CQC's assessment framework.<br><br>CQC inspectors ask the following five key questions:<br>
</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-jHkVzv gbyaRg pf-2927_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-2928_">Is the service safe?</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-2930_">Is the service effective?</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-2932_">Is the service caring?</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-2934_">Is the service responsive?</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-2936_">Is the service well-led?</li></ul><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-2938_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-2940_">Is the service safe?
</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Is_the_service_safe_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.jpg?v=1688138906" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Is_the_service_safe_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.jpg?v=1688138906 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Is_the_service_safe_-_Dr_Richard_Dune_500x.jpg?v=1688138906 320w" width="2000" height="1500" alt="Is the service safe? - Dr Richard Dune -" title="Is the service safe? - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-2941_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-2942_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-2944_">Safety is paramount in health and social care settings. The CQC wants to know if service users, such as patients in a hospital or residents in a care home, are protected from abuse and avoidable harm. <br><br>Inspectors will look at aspects like staffing levels, cleanliness, infection control, medication management, and whether incidents are reported and learned from effectively.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-2945_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-2947_">Is the service effective?
</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Is_the_service_effective_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.jpg?v=1688140050" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Is_the_service_effective_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.jpg?v=1688140050 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Is_the_service_effective_-_Dr_Richard_Dune_500x.jpg?v=1688140050 320w" width="2000" height="1333" alt="Is the service effective - Dr Richard Dune -" title="Is the service effective - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-2948_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-2949_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-2951_">Effectiveness is evaluated based on outcomes and people's experiences. Are patients receiving treatments that meet their needs and conform to evidence-based guidelines? Is their pain managed appropriately? Are their nutritional needs met? Does the service promote a balanced lifestyle?<br><br>Inspectors also consider whether staff receive the necessary training to perform their roles and whether the service complies with relevant legislation.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-2952_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-2954_">Is the service caring?
</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Is_the_service_caring_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.jpg?v=1688139612" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Is_the_service_caring_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.jpg?v=1688139612 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Is_the_service_caring_-_Dr_Richard_Dune_500x.jpg?v=1688139612 320w" width="2000" height="1125" alt="Is the service caring - Dr Richard Dune -" title="Is the service caring - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-2955_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-2956_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-2958_">Caring is about the way staff interacts with service users. Do they treat individuals with compassion, kindness, dignity, and respect? <br><br>The CQC will talk to service users and their families, observe interactions and look for evidence that people's emotional and social needs are understood and met.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-2959_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-2961_">Is the service responsive?
</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Is_the_service_responsive_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.jpg?v=1688139713" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Is_the_service_responsive_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.jpg?v=1688139713 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Is_the_service_responsive_-_Dr_Richard_Dune_500x.jpg?v=1688139713 320w" width="3274" height="2205" alt="Is the service responsive - Dr Richard Dune -" title="Is the service responsive - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-2962_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-2963_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-2965_">A responsive service is one that meets people's needs. This involves timely access to care, individualised planning, and the ability to handle complaints effectively. <br><br>The CQC will examine whether services are designed and organised to meet the needs of the diverse population they serve, including those with complex or multiple needs.
</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-2966_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-2968_">Is the service well-led?</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Is_the_service_well-led_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.jpg?v=1688140159" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Is_the_service_well-led_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.jpg?v=1688140159 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Is_the_service_well-led_-_Dr_Richard_Dune_500x.jpg?v=1688140159 320w" width="2979" height="1973" alt="Is the service well-led - Dr Richard Dune -" title="Is the service well-led - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-2969_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-2970_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-2972_">The last key question pertains to leadership and management. The CQC wants to know if the organisation's leadership, management, and governance assure the delivery of high-quality care, encourage learning and innovation, and promote an open and fair culture. They assess the culture within the organisation, the clarity of the vision and values, and how well these are understood by staff at all levels.
</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-2973_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-2975_">Implementation and rating
</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Implementation_and_rating_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.jpg?v=1688139819" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Implementation_and_rating_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.jpg?v=1688139819 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Implementation_and_rating_-_Dr_Richard_Dune_500x.jpg?v=1688139819 320w" width="2040" height="1356" alt="Implementation and rating - Dr Richard Dune -" title="Implementation and rating - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-2976_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-2977_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-2979_">Now that we understand the five key questions, let's delve into how the CQC uses them during inspections.<br><br>The CQC uses a combination of data, information from providers, and feedback from service users and the public to help them decide when, where, and what to inspect. Once on-site, inspectors use these five key questions to structure their investigation. <br><br>They speak with service users, staff, and managers and observe care to gather evidence against each key question.<br><br>Once the evidence has been collected, each question is rated on a four-point scale:<br>
</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-jHkVzv gbyaRg pf-2980_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-2981_">Outstanding</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-2983_">Good</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-2985_">Requires improvement</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-2987_">Inadequate.</li></ul><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-2989_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-2991_">The ratings for each of the five key questions contribute to an overall rating for the service. This rating is then published, alongside a detailed report, providing a comprehensive picture of what the service does well and where it needs to improve.<br>
</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-2992_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-2994_">Conclusion</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/What_are_the_five_key_questions_asked_by_the_CQC_-_Conclusion_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.jpg?v=1688139923" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/What_are_the_five_key_questions_asked_by_the_CQC_-_Conclusion_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.jpg?v=1688139923 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/What_are_the_five_key_questions_asked_by_the_CQC_-_Conclusion_-_Dr_Richard_Dune_500x.jpg?v=1688139923 320w" width="3579" height="2389" alt="What are the five key questions asked by the CQC - Conclusion - Dr Richard Dune -" title="What are the five key questions asked by the CQC - Conclusion - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-2995_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-2996_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-2998_">The CQCâ€™s five key questions provide a comprehensive framework that captures the essence of what high-quality care should look like. By understanding these five key areas, health and social care services can ensure they are delivering the highest possible standard of care and that their <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/collections/cqc-compliance-training-courses/products/preparing-for-a-cqc-inspection-for-staff-level-1?variant=40437190852677" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);">staff</span></i></a> and <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/collections/cqc-compliance-training-courses/products/preparing-for-a-cqc-inspection-for-managers-level-3?variant=40437196095557" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);">managers</span></i></a> are prepared for their next CQC inspection.
